# Instructions for Non-Coders: The simplest way to set up and run the European Commission Press Corner Scraper


*********Unless otherwise stated, all downloadable files are found in this github page (EU-Commission-Speech-Scraper).************

---

## 1. Install Python

- Go to [python.org/downloads](https://www.python.org/downloads/)
- Download the latest Python version for Windows.
- Run the installer. **Check the box "Add Python to PATH"** before clicking "Install Now".

---

## 2. Install Google Chrome

- Go to [google.com/chrome](https://www.google.com/chrome/)
- Download and install Chrome if you don’t have it.

---

## 3. Install ChromeDriver

- Go to [chromedriver.chromium.org/downloads](https://chromedriver.chromium.org/downloads)
- Download the version that matches your Chrome browser.
- Extract the file.
- Move the `chromedriver.exe` file to the same folder as your scraper files (or note its location).

---

## 4. Download the Scraper Files

- Download or copy all the files (`scraper.py`, `run_parallel.py`, etc.) into a folder on your computer (for example, `C:\Users\<yourname>\Desktop\scraper`).

---

## 5. Install Git Bash

- Download Git Bash from [gitforwindows.org](https://gitforwindows.org/) and install it.
- Open Git Bash from your Start menu.

---

## 6. Open Git Bash and Navigate to Your Scraper Folder

- In Git Bash, type:
  ```bash
  cd "/c/Users/<yourname>/Desktop/scraper"
  ```
  Replace `<yourname>` with your Windows username.

---

## 7. Install Python Packages

- In Git Bash, type:
  ```bash
  pip install selenium requests
  ```

---

## 8. Run the Scraper --- Top Tip!!! Do not use Ursula von der Leyen to test the scraper, unless you're using less than one year intervals - use someone with less speeches like "Stéphane Séjourné" "Jozef Síkela"  "Piotr Serafin"

- To run for a single commissioner, type:
  ```bash
  python scraper.py --commissioner 881 --commissioner-name "Henna Virkunnen" --start-date 01-03-2026 --end-date 07-03-2026 --policy-area "Climate action" --headed
  ```
- To run for multiple commissioners in parallel, type:
  ```bash
  python run_parallel.py --include "Ursula von der Leyen" "Henna Virkkunen" --start-date 01-03-2026 --end-date 07-03-2026 --policy-area "Climate action" --headed
  ```

To add or take away commissioners/policy areas/dates input command like the one above into co-pilot and ask for a return of a command commands with different variables. You can also ask it for e.g. "create commands like this "example command here" for  commissioner x, y, z.. and date range a; "date range b etc; policy area a; policy area b etc..." 
---

## 9. Find Your Downloads

- After the script finishes, look in your scraper folder for new directories named after commissioners and policy areas.
- PDFs will be inside these folders.

---

## 10. Troubleshooting

- If you see errors about ChromeDriver, make sure `chromedriver.exe` is in your scraper folder.
- If you see errors about Python, make sure you installed Python and added it to PATH.
- If you see errors about missing packages, repeat step 7.
- Ask co-pilot for assistance if needed

